Wilbur F. Rose v. Charles Barclay, Appellant, and The Camden Gas Light Company.
Argued March 24, 1899.
Appeal, No. 73, Jan. T., 1899, by Charles Barclay, one of the defendants, from decree of C. P. No. 4, Phil a. Co., March T., 1894, No. 1348, on bill of equity.
